{
  "stem": "18665.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 195.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We watched some of the parades even from their window, because they were right in the center of town.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Fortunately, they never came to our apartment because they were rounding up Jews wherever they found them, in the streets.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Anybody who looked Jewish, we all needed to have identification cards.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was very easy once we showed the card that we were Jews, and then were hauled away, at that time, to the police station, and then jails.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was no concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was no-- except that we knew of concentration camps, but they were not yet extermination camps.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were concentration camps where people who had acted against the laws of the Third Reich, which was trumped up charges anyway, most of the time.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But they will hauled, at that time, to the police station, in order to-- and that is strictly my observation.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "At that time, the Germans did not want the bodies.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They just wanted the people to leave and leave their belongings.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Their apartments, their business, their cars, their, their furniture, whatever they owned.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that was a way of forcing the wives to make all the arrangements.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And once they showed that they have exit visas and they had the passport for those who were in jail, that they could-- they were then let out to leave.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Some of them I saw him on board ship.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They still came with shaven hair, right straight from the, from jail.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But fortunately, like I said, we were never caught.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Two weeks later, everything simmered down and we finally went back home.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we left in April of '39.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so it was several months, and I finished my, my-- actually, I went back to work and finished my apprenticeship on January 6, 1939.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
